\taxon{Slogan}
\title{Views are top-level functions}
\import{prelude}

\p{In the [queries](001H), we saw several usages of the pattern}

\pre{%
\kw{def} query (m : T) : Set := ...
}

\p{\code{\kw{def}} is in fact a much more general construct; any theory can replace \code{Set} on the right, and we can take in multiple arguments.}

\p{In general, this allows one to create a \em{view} of a model one theory, in the form of a model of another theory.}
